    <!-- ══════════════ §6.4.1 RATIONALE ══════════════ -->
    <div class="dp-section" id="rationale">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§6.4.1</div>
        <h2>Rationale — The Anchor Effect</h2>
      </div>

      <p>
        When an operator transitions from the Authentication Gateway into the main workspace,
        a jarring colour shift — dark login to bright dashboard — forces the brain to
        <em>re-orient</em>. In a high-stakes environment where a single mis-click can affect
        a sovereign currency balance, unnecessary cognitive effort is a security risk.
      </p>
      <p>
        A consistent theme creates an <strong>Anchor</strong>: the operator does not have to
        "re-learn" the UI between session states. Colours remain the same across:
      </p>

      <div style="display:flex;gap:0;align-items:center;margin:24px 0;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <div class="flow-step" style="margin:0;">
          <div class="flow-num">1</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-weight:700;font-size:13px;">Splash Screen</div>
            <div style="font-size:11px;color:#666;">SovereignNavy background</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="flow-step" style="margin:0;">
          <div class="flow-num">2</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-weight:700;font-size:13px;">Authentication Gateway</div>
            <div style="font-size:11px;color:#666;">SlatePanel header · ActionBlue button</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="flow-step" style="margin:0;">
          <div class="flow-num">3</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-weight:700;font-size:13px;">Main Workspace</div>
            <div style="font-size:11px;color:#666;">SlatePanel menu bar · SovereignNavy MDI</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="flow-step" style="margin:0;">
          <div class="flow-num">4</div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-weight:700;font-size:13px;">Issuance Desk</div>
            <div style="font-size:11px;color:#666;">ActionBlue active tab · MintGreen success</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="dp-callout dp-ok">
        <span class="dp-ci">🏛</span>
        <div>
          For a sovereign platform serving Africa's digital money, consistency is a proxy
          for security. A unified palette signals a singular, integrated, hardened system —
          not a collection of loosely bolted tools.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ══════════════ §6.4.2 COLOUR PALETTE ══════════════ -->
    <div class="dp-section" id="palette">
      <div class="dp-section-header">
        <div class="dp-section-num">§6.4.2</div>
        <h2>The "Sovereign Navy" Colour Palette</h2>
      </div>

      <p>
        Six tokens cover every surface in the application. All QSS stylesheets must
        reference only these values — no ad-hoc colours.
      </p>

      <div class="swatch-row">
        <div class="swatch" style="background:#0B1E2D;">
          <div class="swatch-name">Sovereign Navy</div>
          <div class="swatch-var">@SovereignNavy</div>
          <div class="swatch-hex">#0B1E2D</div>
          <div class="swatch-use">Primary background · Login · MDI workspace</div>
        </div>
        <div class="swatch" style="background:#1C252C;">
          <div class="swatch-name">Slate Panel</div>
          <div class="swatch-var">@SlatePanel</div>
          <div class="swatch-hex">#1C252C</div>
          <div class="swatch-use">Menu bar · Sidebars · Login header · Status ribbon</div>
        </div>
        <div class="swatch" style="background:#1565C0;">
          <div class="swatch-name">Action Blue</div>
          <div class="swatch-var">@ActionBlue</div>
          <div class="swatch-hex">#1565C0</div>
          <div class="swatch-use">Primary buttons · Active tabs · Focus border</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="swatch-row">
        <div class="swatch" style="background:#27AE60;">
          <div class="swatch-name">Mint Success</div>
          <div class="swatch-var">@MintSuccess</div>
          <div class="swatch-hex">#27AE60</div>
          <div class="swatch-use">Active-tab accent border · Section labels · Governance approval · Logo "Q" green</div>
        </div>
        <div class="swatch" style="background:#4A5568;">
          <div class="swatch-name">Text Primary</div>
          <div class="swatch-var">@TextPrimary</div>
          <div class="swatch-hex">#FFFFFF</div>
          <div class="swatch-use">High-contrast text on dark backgrounds</div>
        </div>
        <div class="swatch" style="background:#2A3640;">
          <div class="swatch-name">Text Secondary / Border</div>
          <div class="swatch-var">@TextSecondary / @Border</div>
          <div class="swatch-hex">#A0AAB4 / #2A3640</div>
          <div class="swatch-use">Muted labels · Timestamps · Field borders · Separators</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Supplementary Tokens</h3>
      <div class="dp-table-wrap"><table class="dp-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Hex</th><th>Usage</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>InputBg</code></td><td><code>#141D26</code></td><td>Input field background — darker than SovereignNavy for depth cue</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>ActionBlueHover</code></td><td><code>#1976D2</code></td><td>Button hover state — lighter lift on ActionBlue</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>ActionBluePressed</code></td><td><code>#0D47A1</code></td><td>Button pressed / active state</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>DangerRed</code></td><td><code>#B71C1C</code></td><td>Error states · Quarantine alerts · Lockdown button</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>LoginGradientCenter</code></td><td><code>#162E44</code></td><td>Radial gradient center on login — slightly lighter than SovereignNavy</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <div class="dp-callout dp-warn" style="margin-top:20px;">
        <span class="dp-ci">⚠</span>
        <div>
          <strong>No ad-hoc colours.</strong> If a new panel or dialog requires a colour
          not listed above, submit a design change request. Introducing one-off hex values
          fragments the palette and breaks the Anchor Effect for operators.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

